    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve  tried making this recipe 3 times and it came out kind of &#8220;rubbery&#8221;.  I made it again and left out the honey and the oil, and added 1/3 cup each of sesame seeds, poppy seeds, and ground flax seeds.  Then toasted it as directed and it has the crispy consistency<br />I was looking for.  I don&#39;t add honey when I&#39;m eating it, but add fruit instead &#8212; grapes are wonderful with it especially in the fall.</p>
    </div>

